  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for glibc",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for glibc fixes the following issues\n\n- CVE-2026-4046: assertion failure when converting inputs may be used to remotely crash an application (bsc#1261206).\n- CVE-2026-5450: stdio-common: scanf %mc pattern will cause heap overflow when width \u003e 1024 (bsc#1262465).\n- CVE-2026-5928: libio: ungetwc could be used to leak data on special conditions (bsc#1262464).\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
